hecks for each bar element if it has an ancestor foo element, that might me=
an climbing up the tree to the very root node. Processing <code>foo&gt;bar<=
/code>, the engine checks for each bar element if its parent element is of =
type foo, that means climbing up the tree just one level.</p><p>(2) kangax =
said, <q>In both Opera and WebKit, <code>[type=3D"..."]</code> selectors se=
em to be more expensive than <code>input[type=3D"..."]</code>. Probably due=
 to browsers limiting attribute check to elements of specified tag (after a=
ll, <code>[type=3D"..."]</code> IS a universal selector).</q><br>The same s=
hould apply to <code>[class~=3D"quz"]</code> vs. <code>foo[class~=3D"quz"]<=
/code>, i.e. to <code>.quz</code> vs. <code>foo.quz</code>, shouldn=E2=80=
=99t it?</p><p>However, the linked to <a href=3D"https://disq.us/url?url=3D=
https%3A%2F%2Fdeveloper.mozilla.org%2Fen%2FWriting_Efficient_CSS%23Don.E2.8=
0.99t_qualify_Class_Rules_with_tag_names%3AlGSHBShZ6d733BCQiAgcG4II-ac&amp;=
