a.org/en/Writing_Efficient_CSS#Don.E2.80.99t_qualify_Class_Rules_with_tag_n=
ames">MDN article</a> says: <q>Don=E2=80=99t qualify Class Rules with tag n=
ames</q>.<br>Now I=E2=80=99m confused. Do engines treat classes different t=
hat other attributes?</p></div></div><span class=3D"post-media"><ul data-ro=
