iv class=3D"post-message " data-role=3D"message" dir=3D"auto"><div><blockqu=
ote>Quoted attribute values vs. unquoted ones (e.g. [type=3Dsearch] vs [typ=
e=3D"search"]). How does this affect performance of selector matching?</blo=
ckquote><p></p><p>The <a href=3D"http://disq.us/url?url=3Dhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.=
w3.org%2FTR%2Fcss3-selectors%2F%23attribute-representation%3AX8vBafF7ydtx46=
SRakCs-yT8-hs&amp;cuid=3D2767575" rel=3D"nofollow noopener" title=3D"http:/=
/www.w3.org/TR/css3-selectors/#attribute-representation">spec says</a>:</p>=
<p></p><blockquote>Attribute values must be CSS <a href=3D"http://disq.us/u=
rl?url=3Dhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2FTR%2FCSS21%2Fsyndata.html%23value-def-id=
entifier%3Az-HRvO_AUCvupfvi6zLUP8_diLM&amp;cuid=3D2767575" rel=3D"nofollow =
noopener" title=3D"http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/syndata.html#value-def-identi=
fier">identifiers</a> or strings.</blockquote><p></p><p>Use quotes. Consist=
ency is more important than a potential 1msec gain. (I don't expect that th=
ere is any difference.)</p><p>A minifier (or some other kind of automated p=
rocess) could remove quotes if they aren't required.</p><p>Also, the perfor=
mance of <code>text-shadow</code> depends on the size of the affected area =
and the blur radius. For example if you give <code>html</code> an inset box=
 shadow with a very large radius (like 300px), it will take bloody ages to =
render.</p><p>I use the star filter for targeting IE7 (e.g. <code>*zoom:1;<=
/code>). CSS properties can't start with a '*'. There will never be a colli=
sion. It's fine, really.</p><p></p><blockquote>Perhaps in the future tools =
like SASS could optimize declarations like these out of the main file and i=
nto conditionally-included ones.</blockquote><p></p><p>Some sort of media q=
uery perhaps? <code>@media (-sass-export: ie7) {zoom: 1;}</code> or somethi=
ng like that.</p></div></div><span class=3D"post-media"><ul data-role=3D"po=
